description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amblescroft South Ward, Salisbury needs you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amblescroft South&lt;/strong&gt; is looking to recruit Staff Nurses to work in our purpose built short-term Mental Health Older person’s assessment unit. This is an active, enjoyable and rewarding Staff Nurse role within a team applying person centred assessment for people experiencing changes in needs due to their illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting role requires you to plan, provide, communicate and evaluate the care outlined within each person’s behavioural support plan. Alongside providing direct care, you will be assisting in admission screening, performance compliance and discharge planning. You will model best practice to other staff and provide support through supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team, we are committed to supporting staff who are newly qualified, experienced or returning to nursing. We would welcome candidates with an interest in the application of current research, psychosocial models of care and environmental adaptations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Jason Fisher, Ward Manager on jasonfisher@nhs.net or 01722 820150&lt;/p&gt;
